formElement.documentation: It is the name of the EMCS console that is used to issue the command. The name must be 2 - 8 characters long, and cannot be defcn, which is reserved.
formElement.label: Consolename:

formElement.documentation: Indicates that the name of the console that is used to issue the command is generated by the REST Console API, by adding CN to the logon user ID. For example, if the logon user ID is CJOEY, the console name is CJOEYCN. If the user ID is longer than 6 characters, the user ID is truncated. For example, if the user ID is ZOSMFAD, then the console name is ZOSMFACN.
